00:16:37.993 --> 00:16:42.933
data, meaning it’s easy to find out where and when an event happened.

00:16:43.743 --> 00:16:48.713
Bellingcat also uses more complicated techniques, large datasets and

00:16:48.973 --> 00:16:53.693
algorithms to trawl through public data and try to seek the truth.

00:16:54.353 --> 00:17:01.293
And as a result, it is now one of the first resources that intelligence services turn to, it

00:17:01.303 --> 00:17:08.463
has received multiple awards, and as of the time of recording it had a full-time team of 18

00:17:08.653 --> 00:17:15.193
full-time employees and more than 30 contributors in over 20 different countries, and thousands

00:17:15.193 --> 00:17:21.963
more volunteers who help comb through publicly available information and try to expose the truth.

00:17:22.723 --> 00:17:27.603
While it might be popular in the West, there’s one country in particular, or at

00:17:27.603 --> 00:17:32.323
least the government of one country, where Bellingcat does not have many friends.

00:17:32.923 --> 00:17:34.383
And that’s Russia.

