of being the information warfare department of MI6, of the British Intelligence

00:17:54.303 --> 00:18:00.633
Services, and said that it is a way for the West to publicly distance itself from

00:18:00.633 --> 00:18:06.793
its information-gathering activities while exposing dirt on and embarrassing Russia.

00:18:07.423 --> 00:18:13.393
Now, of course would be an explosive theory, but there seems to be little truth to it.

00:18:14.353 --> 00:18:20.813
Bellingcat continues to expose crimes and injustices committed by countries all over the world,

00:18:21.143 --> 00:18:28.083
including the US and its allies, and Russia is certainly not the only target of its investigations.

00:18:28.733 --> 00:18:30.353
It’s certainly convenient, though.

00:18:30.913 --> 00:18:37.823
While UK or US intelligence services are often cautious about revealing what they know,

00:18:38.273 --> 00:18:43.843
because their enemies will be able to investigate how they found out, if Bellingcat

00:18:43.893 --> 00:18:49.053
comes out and says something, and explains how it discovered this through public

00:18:49.063 --> 00:18:55.093
information, then that’s hugely advantageous for the “official” secret service divisions.

00:18:56.293 --> 00:19:00.263
What’s more, Bellingcat has shown that it’s prepared to use

00:19:00.263 --> 00:19:04.813
techniques that government departments, at least officially, are not.

00:19:05.633 --> 00:19:12.923
As part of the Skripal investigation Bellingcat bought black-market passport data, and it

00:19:12.943 --> 00:19:18.173
isn’t afraid to do things that would get a government in a lot of trouble if it were caught.

00:19:19.133 --> 00:19:22.983
The example of the citizen detective is a one that is

00:19:23.003 --> 00:19:26.393
